---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Join the Movement - JPMC Workers Alliance">
  <!-- Hero Section -->
  <section class="relative bg-gradient-to-br from-jpmc-gold via-jpmc-gold-500 to-jpmc-gold-700 py-20 rounded-3xl">
    <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-gradient-to-br from-jpmc-gold-800/30 to-jpmc-gold-900/40"></div>
    <div class="relative container mx-auto px-4 text-center text-white">
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto text-gray-100 drop-shadow-lg drop-shadow-gray-900">
        <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-6xl font-bold mb-6 text-gray-50">Join the Movement!</h1>
        <p class="text-xl md:text-2xl mb-8 ">
          Become part of the JPMC Workers Alliance and help build better working conditions for all.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Eligibility Section -->
  <section class="py-16 bg-white">
    <div class="container mx-auto px-4">
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
        <div class="bg-jpmc-blue bg-opacity-10 p-8 rounded-lg border-l-4 border-jpmc-blue">
          <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-6 text-gray-100">Can I Join?</h2>
          <p class="text-lg text-gray-200 mb-4">
            Most employees and contractors can join. Only managers and supervisors cannot.
          </p>
          <p class="text-gray-200 mb-4">
            The company has a few people who seem to blur the line between management and labor, 
            especially at the very lowest levels.
          </p>
          <a href="/mgr" class=" text-gray-100 hover:text-primary-light font-semibold">
            Here's a guide to help you determine your eligibility →
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- How to Join Section -->
  <section class="py-16 bg-jpmc-gray-50">
    <div class="container mx-auto px-4">
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
        <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-center mb-12 text-jpmc-dark">
          How Do I Join?
        </h2>
        
        <div class="bg-white p-8 rounded-lg shadow-lg mb-8">
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-jpmc-red mb-6">In a perfect world:</h3>
          <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 mb-6">
            In a perfect world, you'd be greeted by a union steward when you join the company (or team)
            and shown all the ropes, including how to take advantage of whatever your collective-bargaining-unit has already won.
            <em>The world is far from perfect so far, but we're trying to get it closer every day.</em>
          </p>
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-jpmc-red mb-6">With an established chapter:</h3>
          <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 mb-6">
            Your location <em>may</em> have an active chapter that meets regularly, perhaps for lunch.
            They might even display signs during.
            In that case, go up and introduce yourself.
            Feel free to ask many questions. We don't bite (unless you ask <em>very</em> nicely)
            but we might ask you to help with the next outreach event.
            Expect to show your badge and get looked up soon enough, because we do report improper management behavior to proper authorities.
          </p>
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-jpmc-red mb-6">Building towards a chapter:</h3>
          <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 mb-6">
            Otherwise, the best way is to <a href="https://discord.gg/BZA3pxppq9" target="blank">join our discord</a>.
            There's a brief application process and an online interview, generally including a challenge
            to establish that you are indeed who you say you are. Then you can expect some orientation,
            and finally the opportunity to meet other vetted members from the same region or office.
            The goal is to find like-minded people and build toward one of the earlier scenarios.
          </p>
        </div>

        <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-center mb-12 text-jpmc-dark">
          I'm in! Now how Do I Advance the Cause?
        </h2>
        <!-- Step One -->
        <div class="bg-white p-8 rounded-lg shadow-lg mb-8">
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-jpmc-red mb-6">Step One: Form Strong Social Bonds with Genuine Workers</h3>
          
          <!-- <div class="bg-jpmc-red bg-opacity-10 p-6 rounded-lg mb-6">
            <p class="text-lg text-gray-200 mb-4">
              The CEO seems to want us insular, divided, and defeated -- in short, powerless. 
              That is why we've been conditioned to leave off socializing with work colleagues; 
              to treat the relationship as one of strictly business. To borrow a phrase, it's semi-diseased.
            </p>
            <p class="text-lg text-gray-200">
              By rebuilding the social relationships that might have formed naturally in a healthier environment, 
              we begin to heal ourselves. We begin to form community. We begin to unite. For <strong>United, We Stand!</strong>
            </p>
          </div> -->

          <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
            <div>
              <h4 class="text-lg font-semibold text-jpmc-dark mb-3">What You Can Do:</h4>
              <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
                <li class="flex items-start">
                  <span class="text-jpmc-red mr-2">•</span>
                  Get to know your colleagues as people, not mere cogs in a machine
                </li>
                <li class="flex items-start">
                  <span class="text-jpmc-red mr-2">•</span>
                  Include members of your own team, others you collaborate with
                </li>
                <li class="flex items-start">
                  <span class="text-jpmc-red mr-2">•</span>
                  If possible, eat together (avoid clique behavior)
                </li>
                <li class="flex items-start">
                  <span class="text-jpmc-red mr-2">•</span>
                  Coordinate non-work activities among this social group
                </li>
              </ul>
            </div>
            <div>
              <h4 class="text-lg font-semibold text-jpmc-dark mb-3">Organizing Safely:</h4>
              <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
                <li class="flex items-start"> <span class="text-jpmc-blue mr-2">•</span> Do not disrupt people actively working. </li>
                <li class="flex items-start"> <span class="text-jpmc-blue mr-2">•</span> Do not neglect your own productivity. </li>
                <li class="flex items-start"> <span class="text-jpmc-blue mr-2">•</span> Arrange to meet people away from their desks. </li>
                <li class="flex items-start"> <span class="text-jpmc-blue mr-2">•</span> Choose non-work places and times like break rooms, coffee and lunch breaks. </li>
                <li class="flex items-start"> <span class="text-jpmc-blue mr-2">•</span> Maintain group harmony. A disruptive person can be a liability. </li>
                <li class="flex items-start"> <span class="text-jpmc-blue mr-2">•</span> Get training. We have regular online meetings and love to share. </li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>


        <!-- Step Two -->
        <div class="bg-white p-8 rounded-lg shadow-lg mb-8">
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-jpmc-gold mb-6">Step Two: Expansion and Outreach</h3>
          
          <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 mb-6">
            There's power in numbers, so let's get numbers. Courage is contagious, so show off your union spirit where colleagues can see.
          </p>
          
          <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
            <div>
              <h4 class="text-lg font-semibold text-jpmc-dark mb-3">Community Engagement:</h4>
              <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
                <li class="flex items-start">
                  <span class="text-jpmc-red mr-2">•</span>
                  Join the weekly meetings
                </li>
                <li class="flex items-start">
                  <span class="text-jpmc-red mr-2">•</span>
                  Post more in the community
                </li>
                <li class="flex items-start">
                  <span class="text-jpmc-red mr-2">•</span>
                  Bring in more friends/colleagues
                </li>
                <li class="flex items-start">
                  <span class="text-jpmc-red mr-2">•</span>
                  Participate in planning and executing events
                </li>
              </ul>
            </div>
            
            <div>
              <h4 class="text-lg font-semibold text-jpmc-dark mb-3">Active Participation:</h4>
              <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
                <li class="flex items-start">
                  <span class="text-jpmc-blue mr-2">•</span>
                  Help out in the breakout committees
                </li>
                <li class="flex items-start">
                  <span class="text-jpmc-blue mr-2">•</span>
                  Share ideas, or take initiative
                </li>
                <li class="flex items-start">
                  <span class="text-jpmc-blue mr-2">•</span>
                  Be part of the flyering campaign
                </li>
                <li class="flex items-start">
                  <span class="text-jpmc-blue mr-2">•</span>
                  Show up for lunchtime meetups
                </li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>
          
          <div class="bg-jpmc-dark text-white p-6 rounded-lg mt-6">
            <h4 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-3 text-gray-50">Additional Ways to Get Involved:</h4>
            <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-300">
              <li>• Wear or display union-logo buttons/magnets/keychains</li>
              <li>• Learn and practice <a href="/aeiou" target="blank">organizing conversations</a> with your colleagues.</li>
              <li>• Post about us on social media and relevant sites</li>
              <li>• Share conversations with coworkers in the community</li>
              <li>• Build out a list of union-eligible colleagues in your bargaining unit</li>
              <li>• Equip yourself with business cards and know-your-rights materials</li>
              <li>• Join in on the carpooling effort and entice people to join while you commute</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
        
        
        
        <!-- Step Three -->
        <div class="bg-white p-8 rounded-lg shadow-lg mb-8">
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-jpmc-gold mb-6">Step Three: Grow Worker Power</h3>
          <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 mb-6">
            The general idea is to build effective bargaining units that leverage worker solidarity
            to renegotiate terms and conditions of our employment in a way more favorable to the workers.
          </p>
          <div class="bg-jpmc-dark text-white p-6 rounded-lg mt-6">
            <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-300">
              <li>• You need a plan that works with your colleagues, </li>
              <li>• You need your colleagues onboard with the plan, </li>
              <li>• And then you and your colleagues need to execute the plan. </li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 mb-6">
            It's easy enough to say, but the doing will probably require help. One size <em>does not</em> fit all.
            That's one of the key points of <em>JPMC Workers Alliance</em> being a global organization:
            Our online presence lets every bargaining unit coordinate and share resources,
            including professional guidance from the national union organizations with which we've affiliated:
            <a href="https://cwa-union.org" target="blank">CWA</a> in the United States;
            <a href="https://cwu.org" target="blank">CWU</a> in the United Kingdom.
            That's why we so highly recomend <a href="https://discord.gg/BZA3pxppq9" target="blank">joining the Discord</a>
            and becoming an active participant. The community there has developed a strong base of knowledge and understanding.
          </p>  
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Call to Action -->
  <section class="py-16 bg-jpmc-dark text-white">
    <div class="container mx-auto px-4 text-center">
      <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold mb-6 text-gray-100">
        Ready to Make a Difference?
      </h2>
      <p class="text-xl mb-8 text-gray-300 max-w-2xl mx-auto">
        Join thousands of JPMC employees who are standing together for better working conditions. 
        Your voice matters, and together we're stronger.
      </p>
      <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-4 justify-center">
        <a href="https://discord.gg/BZA3pxppq9" target="blank" class="bg-jpmc-red hover:bg-secondary-light text-white font-bold py-4 px-8 rounded-lg transition-colors duration-300">
          Join the Conversation on Discord
        </a>
        <a href="https://actionnetwork.org/forms/jpmcworkers-signup" target="blank" class="bg-jpmc-red hover:bg-secondary-light text-white font-bold py-4 px-8 rounded-lg transition-colors duration-300">
          Subscribe to Updates
        </a>
        <a href="mailto:jpmcworkers@gmail.com" class="bg-transparent border-2 border-jpmc-gold hover:bg-jpmc-gold hover:text-jpmc-dark text-jpmc-gold font-bold py-4 px-8 rounded-lg transition-colors duration-300">
          Contact Us Directly
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout> 